solution.p:
The function \displaystyle y=\frac{8x}{3x+14} is a quotient of two functions, say f(x)= 8x and g(x)=3x+14.  Then taking the derivatives we get f'(x)=8 and g'(x)=3.  Finally, the quotient rule says that 
\left[\frac{f(x)}{g(x)}\right]'=\frac{g(x)f'(x)-f(x)g'(x)}{\left[g(x)\right]^2}
so y'= \frac{(3x+14) \cdot (8)  - (8x)\cdot (3)}{(3x+14)^2}= \frac{112}{(3 x + 14)^2}.

The function \displaystyle y=\frac{x^{10}}{\sqrt{x}+9x^{4}} is a quotient of two functions, say f(x)= x^{10} and g(x)=\sqrt{x}+9x^{4}.  Then taking the derivatives we get f'(x)=10x^{9} and g'(x)=\frac{1}{2\sqrt{x}}+36x^{3}.  Finally, the quotient rule says that 
\left[\frac{f(x)}{g(x)}\right]'=\frac{g(x)f'(x)-f(x)g'(x)}{\left[g(x)\right]^2}
so y'= \frac{(\sqrt{x}+9x^{4}) \cdot (10x^{9})  - (x^{10})\cdot \frac{1}{2\sqrt{x}}+36x^{3}}{(\sqrt{x}+9x^{4})^2}.

