Find an equation of the curve that satisfies 
\frac{dy}{dx} = 24 yx^{5} 
and whose y-intercept is 4.

Note that when the constant in the denominator is not 1, we still can use the geometric series, but we have to multiply by
a form of 1 that helps us.  We'll use \frac{\frac{1}{9}}{\frac{1}{9}}.
\frac{1}{(9+x)}=\frac{\frac{1}{9}}{\frac{1}{9}(9+x)}=\frac{\frac{1}{9}}{1+\frac{1}{9}x}=\frac{1}{9}\cdot \frac{1}{1+\frac{1}{9}x}
